</h3><p class="sc-kHOZwM oQMan pf-154_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Interactive learning captures students' attention and motivates them to participate actively in the learning process. By incorporating interactive elements such as group discussions, simulations, and multimedia resources, educators can create dynamic learning experiences that resonate with diverse learners.
</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-bTfYFJ fFWOZc pf-156_ pf-heading-1-h3">Personalisation</h3><p class="sc-kHOZwM oQMan pf-158_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Interactive learning allows for personalised learning experiences tailored to the individual needs and interests of students. Adaptive learning platforms and differentiated instruction strategies enable educators to cater to various learning styles and abilities, ensuring that each student receives the support they need to succeed.
</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-bTfYFJ fFWOZc pf-160_ pf-heading-1-h3">Collaboration</h3><p class="sc-kHOZwM oQMan pf-162_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Collaborative learning activities promote teamwork, communication, and problem-solving skills among students. By working together on projects and tasks, students learn from each other's perspectives and develop essential 21st-century skills essential for success in today's interconnected world.
</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-bTfYFJ fFWOZc pf-164_ pf-heading-1-h3">Critical Thinking
</h3><p class="sc-kHOZwM oQMan pf-166_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Interactive learning fosters critical thinking skills by challenging students to analyse information, evaluate evidence, and solve problems creatively. By engaging with complex problems and real-world scenarios, students develop the analytical skills they need to thrive in academic and professional settings.
